{"lemma":"أَجْلَبَ","slug":"أَجْلَبَ","root":"ج.ل.ب","root_slug":"ج-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ل-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَجْلَبَ","root":"جلب","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6051"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6051","headword_ar":"اجلب","root":"jlb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, in eleven places, in the latter half of the paragraph.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His camels brought forth males;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) because the males that they produce are driven, or brought, from one place to another, and sold; opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHlb","text_ar":"احلب"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ his camels brought forth females: ” (S:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his camel brought forth a male."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajolabota","text_ar":"اَجْلَبْتَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA A^aHolabota","text_ar":"وَلَا اَحْلَبْتَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May thy camels bring forth males, and may they not bring forth females,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a form of imprecation against a man, implying a wish that he may lose the milk [that he would have otherwise]. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided, helped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assisted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"another. (S, K.) [So, too,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHlb","text_ar":"احلب"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put an amulet into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"julobap","text_ar":"جُلْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which must therefore signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which an amulet is enclosed, as well as an amulet enclosed in a piece of skin: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujolibN","text_ar":"مُجْلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajlb qatabahu","text_ar":"اجلب قَتَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ijolAbN","text_ar":"اـِجْلابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He covered his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qtb","text_ar":"قتب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel's saddle"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"julobap","text_ar":"جُلْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a piece of fresh, moist skin, which he left upon it until it became dry"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and tight"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he covered the head of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qtb","text_ar":"قتب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a piece of kid's,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lamb's, skin, and left it to dry upon it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","T"]}]}}